# Orders

## Create Authenticated Tracking Uri

```shell
curl "<%= config[:host] %>orders/<ID>/authenticted-tracking-uri?bu=<BU>"
  -X POST
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

> JSON Response:

```json
{
  "orderId": 'ORDER_ID',
  "uri" : "https://track.xpo.com/?orderid=..."
}
```

This endpoint can be used to generate an authentucated URI for the XPO Logistics tracking page

### HTTP Request

`POST <%= config[:host] %>orders/<ID>/authenticted-tracking-uri?bu=<BU>`

### URL Parameters

Parameter | Description |  Valid Values |
--------- | ----------- | ---------------- |
ID | The id of the order | - |
BU | The business unit the order belongs to | [Business Units](#business-units) |
